# Fix CLI-Q3: Improve Unknown Command Experience

## Problem

Sentry issue [CLI-Q3](https://sentry.sentry.io/issues/7368412482/) — 183 events, 85 users, escalating. Users run commands that don't exist and get unhelpful errors. Analysis of ~100 events reveals clear patterns.

## Top Patterns from Telemetry

| Pattern | Frequency | Fix |
|---------|-----------|-----|
| `issue events <id>` | ~20 events | Synonym suggestion + file GH issue for new command |
| `issue get/show/details/info` | ~15 events | `show` alias for `view` |
| `issue resolve/update` | ~8 events | Synonym suggestion → `sentry api` |
| `event list` | ~6 events | Synonym suggestion + file GH issue for new command |
| `issue <bare-id>` | ~5 events | `defaultCommand: "view"` on all route maps |
| Old sentry-cli commands | ~5 events | Synonym suggestion |
| `dashboard show` | ~3 events | `show` alias |
| Typos | ~3 events | Already handled by Stricli |

## Changes (4 areas)

### 1. Add `defaultCommand: "view"` to ALL route maps with a `view` subcommand

Add `defaultCommand: "view"` consistently to all 8 route groups so `sentry issue CLI-G5` routes to `sentry issue view CLI-G5` in a single Stricli pass.

**Files to modify:**

| File | Route |
|------|-------|
| `src/commands/issue/index.ts` | `issueRoute` |
| `src/commands/event/index.ts` | `eventRoute` |
| `src/commands/org/index.ts` | `orgRoute` |
| `src/commands/project/index.ts` | `projectRoute` |
| `src/commands/dashboard/index.ts` | `dashboardRoute` |
| `src/commands/trace/index.ts` | `traceRoute` |
| `src/commands/span/index.ts` | `spanRoute` |
| `src/commands/log/index.ts` | `logRoute` |

**Three edge cases to patch in `src/app.ts`** (all use the same argv inspection pattern):

#### Case A: No args (`sentry issue`)

With `defaultCommand`, Stricli routes to `view` with no positional → `UnsatisfiedPositionalError`. Patch in `exceptionWhileParsingArguments`:

```typescript
if (exc instanceof UnsatisfiedPositionalError) {
  const args = process.argv.slice(2);
  const nonFlags = args.filter((t) => !t.startsWith("-"));
  if (nonFlags.length <= 1 && nonFlags[0] && nonFlags[0] in ROUTES_WITH_DEFAULT_VIEW) {
    const route = nonFlags[0];
    const msg = `Usage: sentry ${route} <command> [args]\nRun "sentry ${route} --help" to see available commands`;
    return ansiColor ? warning(msg) : msg;
  }
}
```

`sentry issue --help` is unaffected — Stricli processes `--help` before `defaultCommand`.

#### Case B: Multi-arg synonym (`sentry issue events CLI-AB`)

For tuple-positional commands (issue, org, project), `events` fills the single positional slot, then `CLI-AB` triggers `UnexpectedPositionalError`. Patch in `exceptionWhileParsingArguments`:

```typescript
if (exc instanceof UnexpectedPositionalError) {
  // ... existing plural alias check ...

  // Check if the user typed a known synonym after a route group
  // e.g., "sentry issue events CLI-AB" → suggest alternative
  const suggestion = getSynonymSuggestionFromArgv();
  if (suggestion) {
    const hint = ansiColor ? warning(`\nTip: ${suggestion}`) : `\nTip: ${suggestion}`;
    return `${text_en.exceptionWhileParsingArguments(exc, ansiColor)}${hint}`;
  }
}
```

For array-positional commands (trace, span, log, dashboard, event), all tokens are silently consumed. These fall through to Case C.

#### Case C: Single-arg synonym (`sentry issue events`) or array-swallowed synonym (`sentry trace events abc123`)

The command runs but fails at the domain level (e.g., `ResolutionError: Issue 'events' not found`). Patch in `exceptionWhileRunningCommand`, before the existing `CliError` formatting:

```typescript
if (exc instanceof CliError) {
  const suggestion = getSynonymSuggestionFromArgv();
  if (suggestion) {
    const prefix = ansiColor ? errorColor("Error:") : "Error:";
    const hint = ansiColor ? warning(`Tip: ${suggestion}`) : `Tip: ${suggestion}`;
    return `${prefix} ${exc.format()}\n${hint}`;
  }
  // ... existing CliError formatting ...
}
```

**Shared helper `getSynonymSuggestionFromArgv()`** (in `src/app.ts` or imported from `src/lib/command-suggestions.ts`):
- Read `process.argv.slice(2)`, strip flags
- If `nonFlags[0]` is a known route group AND `nonFlags[1]` exists AND `getCommandSuggestion(nonFlags[0], nonFlags[1])` returns a match → return the suggestion string
- Otherwise return `undefined`

### 2. Add `show` as alias for `view` on every route map

Use Stricli's native `aliases` property. Same 8 files as section 1, add:
```typescript
aliases: { show: "view" },
```

Also add `remove` alias for `delete` on:
- `src/commands/dashboard/widget/index.ts` — `aliases: { remove: "delete" }`
- `src/commands/project/index.ts` — `aliases: { show: "view", remove: "delete" }`

### 3. Create synonym suggestion registry

**NEW file: `src/lib/command-suggestions.ts`**

Static `Map<string, CommandSuggestion>` keyed by `"routeContext/unknownToken"`:

| Key | Suggestion |
|-----|-----------|
| `issue/events` | `sentry issue view <issue-id>` — "To see events for an issue, view the issue details" |
| `issue/resolve` | `sentry api .../issues/{id}/ --method PUT --data '{"status":"resolved"}'` |
| `issue/update`, `issue/set-status`, `issue/close`, `issue/ignore`, `issue/assign` | Similar API suggestions |
| `issue/comment` | API suggestion for commenting |
| `issue/details`, `issue/info`, `issue/get` | `sentry issue view <issue-id>` |
| `event/list`, `event/events` | `sentry issue view <issue-id>` — "Events are scoped to issues" |
| `cli/info` | `sentry auth status` |
| `cli/send-event` | `sentry api .../store/ --method POST` |
| `cli/issues` | `sentry issue list` |
| `cli/logs` | `sentry log list` |
| `dashboard/default-overview` | `sentry dashboard list` |
| `widget/remove` | Already covered by alias, but kept as fallback |

Note: `issue/get`, `issue/show`, `issue/details`, `issue/info` entries serve as fallback — the `show` alias handles `show`, but `get`/`details`/`info` still need the map. With `defaultCommand: "view"`, these will be caught in Case C (the command runs, tries to resolve "get" as an issue ID, fails).

**Also modify `src/app.ts`:**
- Override `noCommandRegisteredForInput` for synonym suggestions on routes WITHOUT `defaultCommand` (e.g., `cli`, `sourcemap`). With `defaultCommand` on the 8 view-routes, `noCommandRegisteredForInput` won't fire for those — but it still fires for `cli/info`, `cli/issues`, etc.
- The ANSI wrapping fix: Stricli wraps in bold-red, our hint resets before `warning()`:
  ```typescript
  ansiColor ? `\n\x1B[39m\x1B[22m${warning(`Tip: ${hint}`)}` : `\nTip: ${hint}`
  ```

